content:
A call center definition file specifies fields and values to define a call center in Salesforce for a particular CTI system. Salesforce uses these files to support integration with multiple CTI vendors.

Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

The default file is included in every CTI adapter installation package and must be imported into Salesforce for the first instance of a call center. Subsequent call centers can be created by cloning the original.

If an organization modifies or builds a new CTI adapter, they must customize the call center definition file to include required information.

Fields specified in the file cannot be modified after import, but their values can be changed within Salesforce.

To create, view sample files, and import files see:

* Creating a Call Center Definition File
* Sample Call Center Definition File
* Importing a Call Center Definition File
title: Service Cloud: Call Center Definition Files
